2. Use case scenario

"User wants to login"

Initial state: User is not logged in and is a registered user

Normal flow: User clicks "Login" and is directed to a new page.
There he/she enters username and password and clicks "Login".
The user is redirected to the start screen of the application and is now logged in.

What can go wrong: The user mistypes the username or password.

Other activities going on at the same time: Database checks the match with the username and password.

End state: The user is logged in.

